# Copy to lattice-repo-root/.basis.credentials (gitignored) and fill in.
#
# BASIS_CONTROLLER_URL is the gRPC endpoint your basis-controller listens on.
# BASIS_PKI_DIR points at a directory with capi-provider.crt, capi-provider.key,
# and ca.crt — the client identity the basis-capi-provider uses to authenticate
# to the controller. The default below matches the Ansible PKI layout in the
# basis repo; override only if your layout is different.
#
# GHCR_USER / GHCR_TOKEN are passed through to `lattice install` and seed the
# `image-registry-credentials` dockerconfigjson Secret. `basis-mgmt.yaml`
# declares a `default` ImageProvider that wraps this Secret and wires it onto
# the basis-capi-provider Deployment (the image at
# ghcr.io/evan-hines-js/basis-capi-provider is private). Token needs
# `read:packages` scope.

BASIS_CONTROLLER_URL="https://10.0.0.206:7443"
# BASIS_PKI_DIR="${REPO_ROOT}/../basis/deploy/ansible/pki"
# GHCR_USER="your-github-username"
# GHCR_TOKEN="ghp_..."  # read:packages scope
